All artwork featured in this digital exhibition was created by seniors in the AP 2D and AP 3D Art & Design courses. We want to acknowledge the impressive dedication and commitment to the arts that has been displayed by all of our seniors, not only through these unprecedented circumstances, but throughout all of their years at Mahwah High School. We are so lucky to have had the opportunity to work with them and we hope to get the chance to celebrate some of their work together in the future.



Link to Exhibition: https://padlet.com/tpizza/6uqxx4ictyrg2hh3

post_text: Today Brielle dropped off 150 mask extenders (aka, ear savers) to Shop Rite in Wyckoff. Mr. Peter Cavo, the store manger, was very excited to receive our donation and couldn’t wait to give them out to his staff. Now, we are working on 200 extenders for the Ramsey Shop Rite! Thank you to those who donated supplies. #MahwahConnects

post_text:
Dear Thunderbirds,

I hope this finds you well.
The Athletic department has opened an online store to raise funds that will go directly to Medical Front line workers as well as First Responders. The store features the Thunderbird Tough- 2020 line of apparel.
Use the link to purchase these terrific items and support our heroes.
https://www.bsnteamsports.com/shop/Mahwah - copy and paste in Chrome for better viewing.
The store will be open until June 5.

We also have a Go Fund Me Account if you prefer to make a straight donation. https://www.gofundme.com/thunderbirds-in-action



Roger Pelletier
Director of Athletics

post_text: Ava LaVigna - Mahwah High School, grade 9 has taken it upon herself to cut and sew face masks in an effort to raise money. With this money, she has partnered with Eons Greek Food in Paramus, NJ to put together healthy and nutritional meals for the frontliners at the Valley Hospital in Ridgewood, NJ. She will continue her journey in hopes to raise more money to then donate to either other hospitals, the Mahwah Police Stations, Fire Houses and even Supermarket Employees. Way to serve. #MahwahConnects

post_text:
Posted @withregram • @mahwahhslax REPOST: Message from our youth director, Jeff Robator, “Kicking off #TBirdSpiritWeekend and couldn’t be more proud of these 20 Thunderbirds who represented #Mahwah and #mahwahlax yesterday as we participated in a national Wall Ball Challenge with 58 teams from 16 different states. PRIDE in seeing the 20 Team Mahwah Boys representing 11 Grad classes from our current @mahwahhslax head coach @tculloty and 2010 grad down to one of our young 2G studs who will be part of the 2030 class! We had participants from: 2010, 2011 (@markglicini MHS grad and now @pll All Star playing for @pllchaos), 2020, 2021(x2), 2022, 2023(x3), 2024, 2025, 2026(x7), 2028 and 2030. Thank you for all who participated and for those who helped organize. Go watch all their videos split over 4 (posts) Quarters yesterday on the @mahwahlax page. #BeTheOne. “

Jeff, thank you for putting this together. As an alum and coach it is great to see the programs working together. The future is bright! Great job boys! I am very proud of you!

post_text:
Author Emily Dickinson——The robin is the one
That interrupts the morn
With hurried, few, express reports
When March is scarcely on.
The robin is the one
That overflows the noon
With her cherubic quantity,
An April but begun.
The robin is the one
That speechless from her nest
Submits that home and certainty
And sanctity are best.
Submitted by Mrs.Amato

Posted @withregram • @mahwahhslax We got together for potentially the last time to give these young men the gear they’ve earned!
Nothing is ever as good or as bad as it may seem; we still have each other, our health, and families. Please stay safe in these unprecedented times. .
It has been a honor and privilege to call myself your coach. You make me, the program, and your families proud. I hope we can go to battle again.
To my seniors...
Thank you for setting the tone and making a difference for the future of this program with your leadership and tenacity, thank you for not taking the first week of practice for granted and thank you for everything you’ve done to help build this program. We will always have unfinished business.

Molon Labe.
Coach Culloty

Go online to http://www.orderyourdeli.com/mahwah and create an account.

Place your customized orders by 9:30 am. You can use your PaySchools Central Mahwah Student ID # to pre-pay.

Your lunch will be waiting for pick up on the cold line in the cafeteria, without you waiting on line!

Students are responsible for paying for all orders created on the site, even if they do not pick them up.

post_text:
If you use the auto-replenish option offered by PaySchools Central, we recommend logging into your account
and making sure you have the feature set to activate.

If you use this feature, you can set your student’s account to replenish funds when the balance reaches a
specific amount. To do this, just follow these steps:
• Visit www.payschoolscentral.com
• Click on “Auto-Replenishment” from the home screen or user menu
• Select the minimum balance you want to have in the account, and choose how
much to add each time their account drops to that level
• Set the date you want this automation to end, and turn on the payment
• Be sure to click “save” once you have everything set up, and PaySchools Central will take care of the rest!
